  "prompt": "How should I fill my first name and last name in a form, when I have my surname as first name in India?",
  "response": "In India, it\u2019s common for the surname (family name) to appear first, followed by the given name (first name). However, when filling out forms, especially international or standardized ones, the order typically follows the Western convention: **First Name (Given Name)** followed by **Last Name (Surname)**.\n\nHere\u2019s how you should fill it out:\n\n1. **First Name (Given Name):** Write your **given name** (the name that is not your surname/family name).\n2. **Last Name (Surname):** Write your **surname/family name**.\n\nFor example:\n- If your name is **Sharma Ramesh**, where **Sharma** is your surname and **Ramesh** is your given name:\n  - **First Name:** Ramesh\n  - **Last Name:** Sharma\n\nIf there\u2019s any confusion or the form allows for flexibility, you can always check the instructions or clarify with the form provider. Some forms also have an option to specify the order of names if needed.",
